          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Streaming"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Streaming is the serving pattern where the server sends each generated token (or a small batch of tokens) to the client as soon as it is produced, rather than waiting for the entire response to be ready. The client can begin rendering text after the first token arrives \u2014 typically 100\u2013500 ms into the request \u2014 instead of waiting the full 5\u201330 s that a long response takes. Streaming is the expected UX for all user-facing LLM products; every major API (OpenAI, Anthropic, Vertex AI) supports it."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
