              {
                "type": "tableCell",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "paragraph",
                    "content": [
                      {
                        "type": "text",
                        "text": "Use HTTP API (not REST API); or switch to WebSocket API"
                      }
                    ]
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "tableRow",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "tableCell",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "paragraph",
                    "content": [
                      {
                        "type": "text",
                        "text": "Vercel Edge Functions"
                      }
                    ]
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "type": "tableCell",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "paragraph",
                    "content": [
                      {
                        "type": "text",
                        "text": "Streaming supported natively"
                      }
                    ]
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "type": "tableCell",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "paragraph",
                    "content": [
                      {
                        "type": "text",
                        "text": "Use ReadableStream response"
                      }
                    ]
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "tableRow",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "tableCell",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "paragraph",
                    "content": [
                      {
                        "type": "text",
                        "text": "Google Cloud Run"
                      }
                    ]
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "type": "tableCell",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "paragraph",
                    "content": [
                      {
                        "type": "text",
                        "text": "Streaming supported natively"
                      }
                    ]
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "type": "tableCell",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "paragraph",
                    "content": [
                      {
                        "type": "text",
                        "text": "Set minimum instances > 0 to avoid cold starts"
                      }
                    ]
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "nginx configuration for streaming"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "nginx"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "location /v1/chat/stream {\n    proxy_pass http://llm_backend;\n    proxy_http_version 1.1;\n    proxy_set_header Connection \"\";\n\n    # Disable response buffering \u2014 critical for SSE\n    proxy_buffering off;\n    proxy_cache off;\n\n    # Increase timeouts to cover long generations\n    proxy_read_timeout 300s;\n    proxy_send_timeout 300s;\n\n    # Force chunk flushing\n    proxy_set_header X-Accel-Buffering \"no\";\n}"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Error Handling in Streams"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "A sync API can return a 4xx/5xx status code in the HTTP response. A streaming API has already sent HTTP 200 and started the body by the time an error occurs mid-generation. The only way to signal a mid-stream error is to send an error event before closing:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "async def token_generator_with_errors(req: ChatRequest):\n    try:\n        async with client.chat.completions.stream(\n            model=req.model,\n            messages=req.messages,\n        ) as stream:\n            async for chunk in stream:\n                delta = chunk.choices[0].delta\n                if delta.content:\n                    yield f\"data: {json.dumps({'delta': delta.content})}\\n\\n\"\n    except Exception as exc:\n        # Send a structured error event; client must check for this\n        error_payload = json.dumps({\"error\": str(exc), \"code\": \"STREAM_ERROR\"})\n        yield f\"data: {error_payload}\\n\\n\"\n    finally:\n        yield \"data: [DONE]\\n\\n\""
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The client must check every event for an "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ],
            "text": "error"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " field, not just check the HTTP status code. A status code of 200 only guarantees the stream started successfully, not that it completed without error."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Streaming with Tool Calls"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "When the LLM calls a tool during generation, the stream emits partial JSON for the tool arguments incrementally. The client must accumulate argument fragments until the tool call is complete before invoking the function:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "import json\nfrom openai import AsyncOpenAI\n\nclient = AsyncOpenAI()\n\nasync def stream_with_tools(messages: list[dict], tools: list[dict]) -> str:\n    \"\"\"Stream a response that may include tool calls; execute each tool when complete.\"\"\"\n    pending_tool_call = None\n    pending_args = \"\"\n    full_content = \"\"\n\n    async with client.chat.completions.stream(\n        model=\"gpt-4o\",\n        messages=messages,\n        tools=tools,\n    ) as stream:\n        async for chunk in stream:\n            delta = chunk.choices[0].delta\n\n            # Text delta\n            if delta.content:\n                full_content += delta.content\n                print(delta.content, end=\"\", flush=True)\n\n            # Tool call delta\n            if delta.tool_calls:\n                tc = delta.tool_calls[0]\n                if tc.id:\n                    # New tool call starting\n                    pending_tool_call = tc\n                    pending_args = \"\"\n                if tc.function and tc.function.arguments:\n                    pending_args += tc.function.arguments\n\n            # Finish reason signals tool call is complete\n            if chunk.choices[0].finish_reason == \"tool_calls\" and pending_tool_call:\n                args = json.loads(pending_args)\n                result = execute_tool(pending_tool_call.function.name, args)\n                # Continue conversation with tool result\n                messages.append({\"role\": \"tool\", \"content\": str(result),\n                                  \"tool_call_id\": pending_tool_call.id})\n                # Recursively stream the continuation\n                return await stream_with_tools(messages, tools)\n\n    return full_content"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "When to Use Streaming"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "Always use streaming for user-facing chat: "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Users expect to see text appearing as it generates. A blank screen for 5 seconds followed by an instant wall of text feels broken even if the total latency is the same."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "Use streaming for long responses in dashboards: "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Report generation, code generation, document summarisation \u2014 anything where the user will wait > 2 s benefits from streaming."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "Skip streaming for machine-to-machine calls: "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "If the caller immediately processes the full response (a classification pipeline, a batch job), streaming adds complexity with no UX benefit."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "Skip streaming when a downstream layer cannot handle it: "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "AWS API Gateway REST APIs, some older CDNs, and certain logging proxies buffer the entire response. Identify all layers in the request path before committing to streaming."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Summary"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Streaming sends each generated token to the client as soon as it is produced via Server-Sent Events (SSE) over a persistent HTTP connection. The primary metric is time-to-first-byte (TTFB) \u2014 the latency to the first visible token, which determines perceived responsiveness. On the server, use an async generator that yields SSE formatted lines and return it as a StreamingResponse with Cache-Control: no-cache and X-Accel-Buffering: no to prevent proxy buffering. On the client, consume the event stream line by line, handle mid-stream error events explicitly (HTTP 200 does not guarantee successful completion), and accumulate tool-call argument fragments before invoking functions. Streaming is mandatory for user-facing chat; optional for machine-to-machine calls where synchronous responses are simpler."
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  }
}